How exactly is that a sin of the movie? What did the movie do incorrectly by having a staircase that the main character had to walk up?


04:40: "Joker stalking. Jalking? Jokalking?" +1 Sin






Showing Arthur glancing at someone from behind a train car door. The scene shows us his is shy and nervous and watches people from afar, how is that a sin?


Then immediately afterward : "This is a great shot, great acting, great set designs, one of the most well-made movies I ever hated" +1 sin!


I feel like I need to make a web series going over this guy's sins as a "critical analyst", because he has some good points, but buries them in nonsensicle jokes to get his "sin number" higher.

snippet.textDisplay:
At the hospital I work at: Heart monitors don't beep on the rhythm of the heartbeat. They are usually silent, or on a different setting they'll give slow beeps. Ranges are set so that when the heart goes below or above a certain threshold, they'll give an alert. When it goes beyond another threshold, the alert will get louder and red lights start flashing. So in this case, it would start beeping the moment the heart would go below 50 or so, and afterwards it would get louder.

What is unrealistic here, is that the heartbeat shouldn't go down like that, it would go up, due to the adrenalin released when you're in an emergency situation. Also, chocking does not happen that fast, it would take quite a while for your heart to stop like that, and you would likely even get arrythmias before it stops (VT/VF). Also, the monitors would be linked to a central desk or something so they could monitor patients at all times. The minute the heartbeat would drop like that, multiple nurses/doctors WOULD come rushing.
